        <p class="TableText">Converts the cursor to Hand mode, which lets you drag areas of the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> around. This is useful when you have zoomed in on  <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">a frame</MadCap:conditionalText> so much that you cannot see all of it in the editor. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Capture/Steps/Using-Hand-Mode-Feature.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Using the Hand Mode Feature</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Mimic/Steps/Using-Hand-Mode-Feature.htm">Using the Hand Mode</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
